<html class="login-bg">
<head>
  <title>Capstone</title>
  <link href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Arimo:400,700' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', params[:controller] %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body class="login-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <nav class="navbar navbar-default">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <!-- Brand and toggle get grouped for better mobile display -->
          <div class="navbar-header">
            <button type="button" class="navbar-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#bs-example-navbar-collapse-1" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="sr-only">Toggle navigation</span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            </button>
            <a class="navbar-brand" id="navbar-brand" href="http://www.foodfeels.org">FoodFeels</a>
          </div>
          <!-- Collect the nav links, forms, and other content for toggling -->
          <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="bs-example-navbar-collapse-1">
            <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
            </ul>
            <ul class="nav navbar-nav navbar-right">
              <li><%= link_to "About", about_path, id: "navbar-about" %></li>
              <li><%= link_to "Log in", "/auth/github", id: "navbar-login" %></li>
            </ul>
          </div><!-- /.navbar-collapse -->
        </div><!-- /.container-fluid -->
      </nav>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-1">
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-10">
        <h1>About FoodFeels</h1>
        <h3>Mission Statement:</h3>
        <p>
          FoodFeels is an application designed to make it easier to keep track of what you are eating and to help you find potential food intolerances. Traditional pen and paper food diaries are time-consuming to keep and it can be difficult to remember to keep them faithfully. FoodFeels is discrete, portable, and sends you reminders when you forget to enter information! FoodFeels also charts your symptoms for you over time, so you can more easily identify potentially problematic foods.
        </p>
        <h3>Technologies:</h3>
        <p>This project is open source and available on <a href="https://github.com/kdefliese/foodfeels">GitHub</a>.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="http://rubyonrails.org/">Ruby on Rails</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.postgresql.org/">PostgreSQL</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://developer.github.com/v3/oauth/">GitHub OAuth</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://sendgrid.com/">Sendgrid</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://www.highcharts.com/">HighCharts</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/elasticbeanstalk/">AWS Elastic Beanstalk</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://getbootstrap.com/">Bootstrap</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.factual.com/products/cpg">The Factual Product API</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://jqueryui.com/">jQuery UI</a></li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Disclaimer:</h3>
        <p>
          FoodFeels is my final project for <a href="http://adadevelopersacademy.org/">Ada Developers Academy</a>. This website is currently under development and is not intended for commercial use. FoodFeels is not intended to replace or provide professional medical help or advice.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-1">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
